All-Day Futures Trend Pullback (EMA + RSI) [v5] is a simple trend-following pullback strategy built for futures. It defines trend direction using a configurable EMA (default 100) and looks for pullback entries using RSI thresholds—going long when price is above the EMA and RSI is at/under the long level, and short when price is below the EMA and RSI is at/over the short level.

Risk management is handled with bracket exits using either fixed ticks or ATR-based stop loss/take profit, with an optional trailing stop. A session filter can be enabled to limit trading hours, and position size is adjustable via a contracts input. The script plots the EMA and marks long/short signals on the chart.
